doctype html
html(lang='en')
  head
    meta(charset='UTF-8')
    meta(
      name='viewport'
      content='width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0, user-scalable=0'
    )
    meta(name='Description' content='Tiny QR Code Generator')
    link(rel='stylesheet' href='style/index.styl')
    link(rel='icon' type='image/png' href='favicon.png')
    title QR Code Painter

  body
    .top-row
      label.displaced(for='input') Input

      #input
        a#select(href='#template-container') +
          #template-container
            a(
              href='#'
              data-template='MATMSG:TO: <email-address> ;SUB: <Subject> ;BODY: <Text>;;'
            ) Email
            a(href='#' data-template='tel:') Phone
            a(href='#' data-template='geo:<lat>,<long>,<alt>') Geolocation
            a(href='#' data-template='WIFI:T:WPA;S: <ssid> ;P: <password> ;;') WiFi
            a(href='#') Cancel
        textarea(
          type='text'
          rows='1'
          placeholder='Enter text here...'
          spellcheck='false'
        )
        button#clear Ã—

    svg(xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg')
      g
    .bottom-row
      a#download(href='javascript:void(0)') Download QR
      a(
        href='javascript:(function()%7Bwindow.open(\'https%3A%2F%2Falexruppert.github.io%2Fqr-code-painter%2F%3Fq%3D\'%2BencodeURIComponent(window.location.href)%2C\'_blank\')%7D)()'
      ) Bookmarklet
      a#open-about(href='#about') About
      a(href='https://github.com/AlexRuppert/qr-code-painter') GitHub
    #about.modal
      div
        a.modal-close(href='#') Close
        h1 About
        p Whenever I wanted to share something via a QR-Code, I got pretty annoyed:
        | Either you need to install something or you use an online tool.
        p And most of those tools in the top search results are full of ads, collect cookies or even send your inputs to a server. Which you probably do not want, especially when you are creating a QR-Code for an email address or Guest-Wifi-Login.
        | So I implemented a QR-Code encoder from scratch (for the fun of it):

        ul
          li Everything runs in <strong>your</strong> browser, your data does not leave your device
          li Open source - Check out the GitHub link
          li No ads, cookies or other annoyances
          li Simple and tiny, loads fast

        p Have fun! ðŸ˜ƒ

        p PS: You can create a <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bookmarklet'>bookmarklet</a> by saving the link at the bottom left as a bookmark to quickly share your current page's url as a QR-Code.

    a#downloader.hidden
    script(src='noIE.js' async)
    script(src='index.ts' async)
